    "Lower F1 scores were obtained by BERT, even though it achieved a precision value of 88.5%, indicating difficulties in learning positive samples.",
    "Our model outperformed ALBERT, the top-performing PMLs baseline model, by approximately 5%.",
    "The receptive field on text graphs is improved by our proposed RDEP, which is more efficient than ALBERT, which incorporates deep LSTMs to gather extensive data.",
    "Nevertheless, the performance of graphbased neural networks on the Qprop dataset was lower, with PEGCN exhibiting the worst accuracy among all baseline models, with only 49.7% accuracy.",
    "Unlike the other datasets, HGAT exhibited robust results in this study, suggesting its appropriateness for fragment-level datasets."
